## ❓ FAQ

### Is it alright for me to make copies/forks/distributes?

Yes, and please let me know about them. Not for any compliance, but I would love to see what others are doing and help me see where things are viewed as missing.

### How often do you update?

Right now pretty regularly. I am still testing the scripts for all the edge cases. Feel free to put issues here: https://github.com/CursedTechnocrat/TechnicianToolkit/issues

### Do you have a KoFi/Patreon?

No, and I don't intend to ever make money off this. For me this is a passion project to help make technician lives easier.

### Why did you start making these?

I wanted some scripts to help automate some of the most boring parts at work and I really dislike a lot of scripts that just give you a "Done" or "Failure" state.

## Disclaimer

These scripts modify system settings and may install updates/software that require a system reboot. **Ensure all unsaved work is backed up before running.** Use at your own risk.
